# Week 2: Understanding Web Technologies, Intro to HTML5 and CSS, Making a Portfolio

## Week 2 Content

### Learning Objectives

- Apply semantic HTML elements for a structured web portfolio.
- Utilize CSS Flexbox for a responsive and flexible layout.

### Assignment: Building Your Web Portfolio

Your task is to create a simple web portfolio using the skills you've learned so far. Focus on using semantic HTML elements for content structure and apply Flexbox in CSS for a responsive layout.

- **Portfolio Assignment Image:** [View Assignment Image](Try-to-make-something-like-this.png)

### Notes

- Refer to the PDF document in this repository titled "Intro-to-HTML5.pdf" for additional guidance on 

### Submission Guidelines

1. Fork this repository.
2. Create a new branch for your work.
3. Commit your changes and push to your fork.
4. Submit a pull request with your completed portfolio.

### Additional Resources

- [MDN Web Docs - HTML](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML)
- [CSS Tricks - A Complete Guide to Flexbox](https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/a-guide-to-flexbox/)
- [W3Schools Flexbox Tutorial](https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_flexbox.asp)

Good luck, and enjoy building your responsive web portfolio using Flexbox!
